-- InterContinental shares rise on bid talk
-- 
-- Mon Jan 22, 2007 3:48am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/22/us-intercontintental-shares-idUSL2275193220070122

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Shares in InterContinental Hotels ( IHG.L ) climb 2 percent to a record high and tops the FTSE 100  .FTSE  leaderboard for a second session in a row, as trader cite continued talk of a private equity bid. 

 "I know there was stake building rumors," one trader said. "There is no smoke without fire, there is obviously something going on." In a regulatory announcement on Monday, InterContinental said Ellerman Corporation had built a 5 percent holding in the company. On Friday, the stock rose amid continued speculation linking Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide ( HOT.N ) or a private equity firm with a bid. At 0836 GMT, shares in InterContinental Hotels Group were 2 percent higher at 1,338.15 pence. InterContinental Hotels Group declined to comment.